{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17415702","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17415702"},"attributes":{"position":59,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-28T09:14:20+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-28T09:14:13+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1261100"}},"session":{"data":{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1261100"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15553"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17535870","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17535870"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T17:00:36+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T17:00:36+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15553"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1261100","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionSessions/1261100"},"attributes":{"startedAt":"2025-09-28T07:52:04+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-28T10:28:52+09:30","sessionType":"qbank","questionStatus":"all","difficulty":[],"timeLimit":null,"questionCount":62,"questionsAnswered":61,"marksTotal":61,"marksAttainable":61,"marksAttempted":61,"finishedAt":"2025-09-28T09:15:31+09:30","resultsAvailable":true,"score":0.2,"questionsCorrect":12,"marksCorrect":12},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"pack":{"data":{"type":"packs","id":"5"}},"exam":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questions","id":"15553","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15553"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.7,0.02,0.05,0.01,0.22]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8244"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"61829"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8244","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8244"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15553"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"47275"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"8"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"8053"},{"type":"tags","id":"8790"},{"type":"tags","id":"8861"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19928"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"61829","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/61829"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 72-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic for a routine check-up as her grandson was worried about the change of colour in her eyes. She has a medical history of well-controlled hypertension and osteoarthritis. Her medications include amlodipine and paracetamol.  Her grandson has regular venesections for a hereditary disease.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, she appears well with vital signs within normal limits. Snellen chart showed 20/30 vision in her left eye and 20/25 in her right eye without aids, which is unchanged from her last routine review. Examination of her eyes reveals bilateral grey-white rings at the periphery of both corneas, with clear central corneas.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Arcus senilis","Osteogenesis imperfecta","Keratoconus","Acute angle closure glaucoma","Haemochromatosis"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with the classic appearance of \u003Cstrong\u003Earcus senilis\u003C/strong\u003E, which is a grey-white ring of lipid deposition in the peripheral cornea. It is a common age-related finding in elderly patients and is typically benign and asymptomatic, requiring no specific treatment. The ring is usually bilateral and symmetric, with a clear zone between the ring and the limbus (lucid interval of Vogt).\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOsteogenesis imperfecta\u003C/strong\u003E is a genetic disorder affecting collagen formation, primarily causing bone fragility. While it can have ocular manifestations including blue sclera, it would not cause a peripheral corneal ring appearance and would have presented much earlier in life with multiple fractures.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EKeratoconus\u003C/strong\u003E is a progressive thinning and cone-like protrusion of the central cornea, typically presenting in young adults with progressive myopia and astigmatism. It does not cause a peripheral ring appearance.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAcute angle closure glaucoma\u003C/strong\u003E presents with severe eye pain, headache, nausea, vomiting, and reduced vision. The cornea appears hazy throughout rather than having a peripheral ring. The pupil is typically mid-dilated and unreactive.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHaemochromatosis\u003C/strong\u003E is a disorder of iron metabolism that can affect multiple organs. While it can have ocular manifestations with brown pigmentation deposits, these typically involve retinal changes rather than corneal rings. The characteristic corneal finding in this case is much more consistent with arcus senilis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhile arcus senilis in patients under 50 years of age may indicate underlying hyperlipidaemia requiring further investigation for cardiovascular risk, in elderly patients like this one, it is considered a normal age-related finding. No specific treatment or investigation is required unless there are other risk factors for cardiovascular disease present.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Arcus senilis is a common age-related finding characterised by a white-grey ring around the corneal periphery.","Arcus senilis in patients over 50 years of age is usually benign and does not require further investigation."],"references":["Weinstein J, Bunya V, Ahmad S.  Arcus Senilis. Eye Wiki. 2024.  Available at: https://eyewiki.org/Arcus_Senilis","Hashemi, H., Malekifar, P., Aghamirsalim, M. et al. Prevalence and associated factors of corneal arcus in the geriatric population; Tehran geriatric eye study. BMC Ophthalmology. 2022.  Available at: https://bmcophthalmol.biomedcentral.com/articles/10.1186/s12886-022-02578-6"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"47275"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15553"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"47275","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/47275"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-16T15:33:42+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-16T15:35:21+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8244"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"61829"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"8","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/8"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc41","name":"Ophthalmology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:45+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"64","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/64"},"attr